        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued March 30 at 11:58PM EDT by NWS Wilmington OH</headline>
        <description>At 1157 PM EDT, a strong thunderstorm was located over Kincaid
Springs, moving east at 65 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 45 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Hail may cause minor damage to
vegetation.

Locations impacted include...
Pike County Airport, Pike Lake, Elm Grove, Omega, Buchanan,
Summithill, Givens, Ladd, Piketon, Londonderry, Waverly, Richmond
Dale, Massieville, Linn, Lake White, Scioto Trail State Park, and
Idaho.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a sturdy building.

A Tornado Watch remains in effect until 100 AM EDT for south central
Ohio.

To report hazardous weather conditions, go to our website at
weather.gov/iln and submit your report via social media, when you can
do so safely.</instruction>
